    "Terms Inhibition, suppression, attentional suppression, attentional enhancement, enhancement effect, suppression effect.",
    "It has long been proposed that visual attention modulates sensory responses to stimuli based upon their features and locations (→ Guidance).",
    "For example, if we are searching a grocery store aisle for a red can of soup, we can restrict attention to red objects to improve the efficiency of our search.",
    "Such attentional guidance was initially proposed to occur via enhancement of task-relevant features and locations (Folk et al., 1992; Wolfe, 1994).",
